==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Penicillamine
<hw>Pen`i*cil"lam*ine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.,
Med.)</fld> <def>A substance (<chform>C5H11NO2S</chform>) which is a
degradation product of the penicillins. Chemically it is
<chname>3-mercapto-D-valine</chname>. It has chelating properties and is
used in medicine as an antirheumatic and to chelate copper in cases of
hepatolenticular degeneration (Wilson's disease).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Penicillate</ent>⟦br⟧
